## Key Insights
Raft decomposes consensus into leader election, log replication, and safety, tolerating (N-1)/2 failures. A hybrid using Paxos flexible quorums for reads and Raft majority for writes could optimize latency.

## Connections
The Raft-Paxos synthesis reveals a design space between strict and flexible quorums. BFT comparison (3f+1 vs 2f+1) adds a fault model dimension.

## Foundation
Raft fault tolerance, leader election timeouts, and Paxos flexible quorums (R+W>N) are well-established.

## Open Questions
Under what partition patterns does Raft's majority requirement cause unnecessary unavailability vs. flexible quorums?